<p>For Arlington's hot-humid climate, HVAC systems with a minimum 16 SEER rating are recommended, though 18+ SEER units provide optimal efficiency for the extended cooling season. Two-stage or variable-speed compressors excel in this climate by running longer at lower speeds, which improves dehumidification while maintaining consistent temperatures. Heat pumps are particularly effective in Arlington since heating demands are moderate, typically only needed from December through February, making year-round heat pump operation more efficient than traditional AC/gas furnace combinations. Systems should include enhanced dehumidification features or whole-home dehumidifiers to manage the high moisture loads common in North Texas summers. For optimal performance, look for units with advanced inverter technology that can adjust output based on real-time conditions, providing superior comfort and energy savings during Arlington's variable weather patterns.</p>

